description:
Ever wonder how @MrBeast and his team come up with their wildest video ideas? Go behind the scenes with the writers' room where no idea is too big. From renting out the Golden Gate Bridge at 4 AM to rolling up with 50 tanks and helicopters, this is where the magic (and chaos) begins.

The process? Blue skyingalways pushing for the best, most ambitious idea possible. And when you need to pull off something as crazy as walking into a bank asking for a million dollars in cash, there's one tool that keeps the whole operation running: @Slackhq.

Want to know if MrBeast has ever blown up a bank? *Just ask Slackbot*. 
Need the address for your next shoot? Someone will Slack it to you. 
This is how the biggest creator on the planet gets things done.

Watch as the team shares their creative process, from pitching Jimmy wild concepts to making last-minute changes on the fly. When you're producing videos at this scale, communication is everythingand Slack keeps everyone connected, no matter how insane the idea gets.

Learn more about how MrBeast uses Slackbot to turn his ideas into actions: https://slack.com/lp/mrbeast 
 Watch more episodes from Inside the Beast: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnobS_RgN7JZAhVg871pjR1varMRLMprh
